snippet.title: Nepal Country is ON FIRE! DANGEROUS Social Media Protest #shorts
snippet.description:
In recent weeks, Nepal has witnessed some of its largest youth-led demonstrations in decades. The protests began after the government suddenly blocked access to popular social media platforms like Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp, and X unless they registered locally. For many young people, this felt like an attack on their freedom of expression and their way of connecting with the world.

What started as anger over the social media ban quickly grew into something bigger. Young Nepalis began voicing frustration over corruption, political favoritism, and the privileges enjoyed by the children of powerful leaders. Online, this anger was captured by the “Nepo Kid” trend, which highlighted the gap between political elites and ordinary citizens.

Crowds of students and young workers gathered across cities, even defying curfews. Their chants and slogans called not only for the return of social media access but also for deeper changes in governance. The protests gained momentum and soon spread across the country, with people demanding more accountability and fairness from their leaders.

As the movement grew, the pressure on the government became impossible to ignore. Prime Minister K. P. Sharma Oli announced his resignation, and other officials followed. The social media restrictions were lifted, but many protesters insisted that this was only the first step. They continue to call for long-term reforms to reduce corruption and ensure that young voices are heard in the country’s future.

This moment has shown the power of Nepal’s younger generation. By standing together, they demonstrated that they can bring about real change. Their energy and determination have reshaped the political conversation in the country, marking the beginning of a new chapter.

snippet.description:
Watch the full episode here - https://youtu.be/2h00Q0Fjah8

“We all have a #MeToo story — we’ve all been through difficult situations on public transport, schools, colleges, and tuitions. While most of us have internalised this whole thing and decided, ‘I’ll be more careful next time,’ there were a few who chose to speak up about their plight. The culprits were named and shamed, and yet, no action was taken. What was the point of it all, then? 
I believe this is why we need more women in positions of power. So those women can lend courage and support to others and tell them, ‘You’re not alone!’”

Currently the Managing Editor of Firstpost, Palki Sharma Upadhyay is not just a name in the world of journalism; she is a beacon of excellence, integrity, and dedication. With her unwavering commitment to truth, her insightful analysis, and her captivating storytelling, Palki has carved a niche for herself in the media industry.

From covering historic elections to reporting from conflict zones, Palki has been on the frontlines, bringing us the news that shapes our world. Her keen investigative skills have led her to unravel complex political scandals, humanitarian crises, and social issues, giving voice to the voiceless and shedding light on the stories that need to be told.

Beyond her professional achievements, Palki Sharma Upadhyay is a strong woman who has challenged and changed the narrative about a ‘working mother’, and aspires to change the way newsrooms work. 

Join us in uncovering Palki Sharma’s journey as she shares her insights, experiences, and the incredible stories she has gathered during her illustrious career. 

We talked about: 
. Finding her calling in journalism
. Childhood days
. Beginning her career with Doordarshan
. Take on the evolution of news
. Ethics in Journalism
. On-ground experiences, reporting from conflict zones
. Take on ‘no news’
. Finding a balance
. Motherhood 
. Feminism in newsrooms
. Self-acceptance
. Idea behind firstpost

FOX News Channel (FNC) is a 24-hour all-encompassing news service delivering breaking news as well as political and business news. The number one network in cable, FNC has been the most-watched television news channel for 18 consecutive years. According to a 2020 Brand Keys Consumer Loyalty Engagement Index report, FOX News is the top brand in the country for morning and evening news coverage. A 2019 Suffolk University poll named FOX News as the most trusted source for television news or commentary, while a 2019 Brand Keys Emotion Engagement Analysis survey found that FOX News was the most trusted cable news brand. A 2017 Gallup/Knight Foundation survey also found that among Americans who could name an objective news source, FOX News was the top-cited outlet. Owned by FOX Corporation, FNC is available in nearly 90 million homes and dominates the cable news landscape, routinely notching the top ten programs in the genre.
